.TH "dma_fence_default_wait" 9 "dma_fence_default_wait" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
dma_fence_default_wait \- default sleep until the fence gets signaled or until timeout elapses
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "signed long" dma_fence_default_wait
.BI "(struct dma_fence *fence "  ","
.BI "bool intr "  ","
.BI "signed long timeout "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "fence" 12
the fence to wait on
.IP "intr" 12
if true, do an interruptible wait
.IP "timeout" 12
timeout value in jiffies, or MAX_SCHEDULE_TIMEOUT
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Returns -ERESTARTSYS if interrupted, 0 if the wait timed out, or the
remaining timeout in jiffies on success. If timeout is zero the value one is
returned if the fence is already signaled for consistency with other
functions taking a jiffies timeout.
